{"name": "aopc", "metadata": {"name": "aopc", "version": "0.1.0", "classifiers": ["Programming Language :: Python :: 3", "Programming Language :: Python :: 3.10", "Programming Language :: Python :: 3.11", "Programming Language :: Python :: 3.12"], "home_page": null, "license": null, "documentation_url": null, "dependencies": ["pydantic", "pydantic-settings", "torch", "transformers", "datasets", "loguru", "numba", "numpy"], "summary": null, "upload_time": 1734085070}, "documentation": ["# Aopc\n\nThe `Aopc` package provides a framework for evaluating model faithfulness using the Area Over the Perturbation Curve (AOPC) metric. It supports Hugging Face models and datasets, specifically tailored for sequence label classification tasks.\n\n## Installation\n\nInstall the package via pip:\n\n```bash\npip install aopc\n```\n\n## Key Features\n\n- **Support for Hugging Face models and datasets**: Utilize pre-trained models and standard datasets seamlessly.\n- **AOPC Evaluation**: Calculate AOPC metrics for attributions.\n- **Beam Size Suggestion**: Automatically estimate optimal beam sizes for normalized AOPC using our approximation method.\n\n## Quick Start\n\n### Initialize the `Aopc` Class\n\nStart by configuring `Aopc` with a Hugging Face model, such as `prajjwal1/bert-tiny`:\n\n```python\nfrom aopc import Aopc\n\naopc = Aopc(model_id=\"prajjwal1/bert-tiny\")\n```\n\n### Evaluate Dataset\n\nLoad your dataset with Hugging Face's `datasets` library and evaluate it with `Aopc`:\n> **Note**: If the dataset has not been tokenized `Aopc` will take care of it.\n```python\nimport datasets\n\n# Load dataset\ndset = datasets.load_dataset(\"stanfordnlp/imdb\")\n\n# Evaluate dataset without normalization\nnew_dset = aopc.evaluate(dset)\n```\n**Note**: `Aopc.evaluate()` allow either a dictionary, datasets.Dataset or datasets.DatasetDict as input.\n\n### Normalized AOPC with Exact Bounds\nEstimate \n\n```python\nnew_dset = aopc.evaluate(dset, normalization=\"exact\")\n```\n\n### Normalized AOPC with Approximated Bounds\nCalculate the suggested beam size for normalized AOPC approximation:\n\n```python\n# Estimate Beam Size\nbeam_size = aopc.get_suggested_beam_size(dset)\n\n# Approximate normalization\nnew_dset = aopc.evaluate_dset(dset, normalization=\"approx\", beam_size=beam_size)\n```\n\n## License\n\nThis project is licensed under the MIT License.\n"], "modules": [{"name": "aopc", "documentation": [], "functions": [], "variables": [], "classes": [], "exports": [{"name": "aopc.Aopc", "xref": {"fqname": "aopc.main.Aopc", "project": null}}, {"name": "aopc.AopcResult", "xref": {"fqname": "aopc.main.AopcResult", "project": null}}]}, {"name": "aopc.main", "documentation": [], "functions": [], "variables": [{"name": "aopc.main.DatasetTypes", "type": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "aopc.main.WordMap", "type": {"name": "typing.TypeAlias", "xref": {"fqname": "typing.TypeAlias", "project": "--std--"}, "params": null}, "documentation": []}, {"name": "aopc.main.NormalizationType", "type": {"name": "typing.TypeAlias", "xref": {"fqname": "typing.TypeAlias", "project": "--std--"}, "params": null}, "documentation": []}, {"name": "aopc.main.DictStrKey", "type": {"name": "typing.TypeAlias", "xref": {"fqname": "typing.TypeAlias", "project": "--std--"}, "params": null}, "documentation": []}, {"name": "aopc.main.TokenId", "type": {"name": "typing.TypeAlias", "xref": {"fqname": "typing.TypeAlias", "project": "--std--"}, "params": null}, "documentation": []}, {"name": "aopc.main.aopc", "type": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "aopc.main.dset", "type": {"name": "datasets.Dataset", "xref": {"fqname": "datasets.Dataset", "project": "datasets"}, "params": null}, "documentation": ["type: ignore"]}, {"name": "aopc.main.tokenizer", "type": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "aopc.main.dset", "type": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "aopc.main.dset", "type": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "aopc.main.result", "type": null, "documentation": []}], "classe